  ('RF-AIM-AISOL-005', 'AI Solution Delivery', 'Delivers AI-enabled solutions by coordinating requirements, data readiness, model or vendor components, integration plans, testing, adoption support, and stakeholder handoff. This role family bridges business users, AI specialists, engineering teams, and governance reviewers to make AI initiatives operationally usable.'),
  ('RF-AIM-DS-001', 'Data Science Experimentation', 'Explores data, designs experiments, develops statistical or machine-learning models, and evaluates whether patterns are strong enough to support business decisions. This role family handles feature exploration, model comparison, validation, bias checks, and evidence-based interpretation before any model is promoted for use.'),
  ('RF-AIM-GENAI-004', 'GenAI Application Design', 'Designs applications that use generative AI capabilities through prompts, retrieval, orchestration, workflows, guardrails, and user experience patterns. This role family converts use cases into safe AI-assisted journeys, tests output quality, handles failure modes, and documents evidence for responsible adoption.'),
  ('RF-AIM-GOV-006', 'Responsible AI Evidence Support', 'Supports responsible AI governance by collecting evidence on data use, model purpose, human oversight, risk controls, bias checks, user disclosures, and approval status. This role family helps teams prove that AI use is documented, reviewed, and aligned with policy before or during deployment.'),
  ('RF-AIM-MLENG-002', 'Machine Learning Engineering', 'Turns validated models into reliable software components and services that can run at scale in production or controlled environments. This role family builds feature pipelines, model-serving interfaces, performance controls, integration logic, and engineering tests needed to make machine-learning outputs usable by applications.'),
  ('RF-AIM-MLOPS-003', 'MLOps and Model Operations', 'Operates the lifecycle of machine-learning models after development, including deployment, monitoring, retraining triggers, drift checks, version control, and rollback readiness. This role family maintains model reliability evidence and coordinates between data science, engineering, platform, and governance stakeholders.'),
  ('RF-BIOMASS-COGEN-OPS', 'Biomass/Bagasse Cogeneration O&M', 'Handles cogeneration plant O&M, boiler/turbine operation, and biomass/bagasse fuel-handling supervision.'),
  ('RF-BPM-AUTO-003', 'Automation-enabled Operations Support', 'Supports business operations that use bots, scripts, workflow automation, and assisted processing tools. This role family validates automation inputs, monitors failed transactions, separates process exceptions from system issues, coordinates fixes, and ensures automated work remains auditable and business-safe.'),
  ('RF-BPM-LEAD-004', 'BPM Team and Queue Control', 'Controls team queues, workload distribution, SLA movement, productivity signals, and exception escalation in BPM environments. This role family monitors capacity, prioritizes urgent work, supports agents, reports queue health, and coordinates with quality, client, and operations leaders to protect service delivery.'),
  ('RF-BPM-OPS-001', 'Digital Process Operations', 'Executes high-volume digital business processes using defined procedures, workflow platforms, client systems, and transaction records. This role family processes requests, validates data, updates cases, handles exceptions within role limits, and maintains evidence that work was completed accurately and on time.'),
  ('RF-BPM-QA-002', 'Process Quality and Transaction Monitoring', 'Reviews completed process transactions to detect errors, compliance gaps, SLA risks, and coaching opportunities. This role family samples work, checks against quality rules, records defects, identifies recurring patterns, and provides evidence for process correction and team performance improvement.'),
  ('RF-CLD-ARCH-001', 'Cloud Architecture and Migration', 'Designs cloud target architectures and migration plans that balance availability, security, cost, performance, and operational manageability. This role family assesses current workloads, defines landing-zone patterns, selects services, plans migration waves, and provides architecture evidence for cloud transformation decisions.'),
  ('RF-CLD-DEVOPS-003', 'Cloud DevOps Engineering', 'Automates build, test, deployment, configuration, and environment-management workflows for cloud-hosted applications. This role family maintains pipelines, infrastructure as code, secrets handling, deployment controls, observability hooks, and rollback readiness to reduce release risk and improve delivery speed.'),
  ('RF-CLD-ENG-002', 'Cloud Platform Engineering', 'Builds and maintains cloud platform foundations such as compute, storage, networking, identity integration, automation, and environment templates. This role family turns architecture into reusable platform services, supports provisioning, manages configuration standards, and improves reliability for application teams using cloud infrastructure.'),
  ('RF-CLD-GOV-005', 'Cloud Governance and FinOps Support', 'Supports responsible cloud usage by checking cost, tagging, policy compliance, access patterns, resource ownership, and consumption trends. This role family prepares FinOps reports, flags waste, validates governance exceptions, and helps teams align cloud consumption with budget, security, and operating standards.'),
  ('RF-CLD-SRE-004', 'Site Reliability and Observability', 'Protects service reliability by monitoring availability, latency, error rates, saturation, incidents, and recovery behaviour across applications and platforms. This role family defines observability signals, investigates production issues, supports incident response, improves runbooks, and reduces recurring service instability.'),
  ('RF-COAL-OPS', 'Coal Thermal O&M and Shift Operations', 'Handles coal thermal O&M and shift operations across boiler, turbine, electrical, C&I, maintenance, and control-room work.'),
  ('RF-CS-001-01', 'SOC Analyst', 'Handles first-line SOC alert review by validating SIEM or EDR signals, checking affected assets and users, recording triage notes, and escalating confirmed security events without overstating incident authority.'),
  ('RF-CS-001-02', 'MDR Analyst / SIEM-SOAR Detection Support', 'Supports managed detection and response operations by enriching SIEM/SOAR cases, coordinating response handoffs, maintaining detection evidence, and routing validated incidents to response or engineering owners.'),
  ('RF-CS-001-03', 'SOC Lead / SOC Operations Lead', 'Controls SOC shift operations by reviewing alert queues, guiding escalation quality, monitoring SLA movement, coordinating handoffs, and ensuring security operations evidence is complete for incident and service review.'),
  ('RF-CS-002-01', 'Cloud Security Engineer', 'Implements and remediates cloud security controls across cloud services, identities, network exposure, logging, encryption, and workload configuration while coordinating safe change execution with platform and application teams.'),
  ('RF-CS-002-02', 'Cloud Security Risk / CNAPP-CSPM Analyst', 'Reviews cloud posture and CNAPP/CSPM findings by validating risk context, ownership, policy guardrails, exposure paths, and remediation evidence for cloud workloads and accounts.'),
  ('RF-CS-002-03', 'Cloud-Native / Container Security Engineer', 'Secures cloud-native workloads by handling container, Kubernetes, image, runtime, and configuration control findings, then coordinating remediation without disrupting approved deployment pipelines.'),
  ('RF-CS-003-01', 'Application Security Engineer', 'Reviews application security findings, validates vulnerability context, supports secure design or code remediation, and prepares release-facing evidence so application teams can close exploitable weaknesses responsibly.'),
  ('RF-CS-003-02', 'Product Security Engineer', 'Supports product security across product architecture, threat modeling, abuse-case review, feature risk handoff, and security acceptance evidence for customer-facing or platform product releases.'),
  ('RF-CS-003-03', 'DevSecOps / AppSec Tooling Engineer', 'Operates DevSecOps and AppSec tooling by managing scanner outputs, dependency risks, CI/CD gate exceptions, evidence packs, and remediation routing for engineering teams.'),
  ('RF-CS-004-01', 'IAM Operations Analyst', 'Executes IAM operations by validating access requests, user lifecycle changes, role assignments, access evidence, and exception routing within approved identity and access control procedures.'),
  ('RF-CS-004-02', 'PAM / IGA Engineer', 'Supports privileged access and governance engineering by handling PAM workflows, IGA configuration evidence, entitlement controls, access review data, and segregation-of-duties signals under approval boundaries.'),
  ('RF-CS-004-03', 'IGA / Access Governance Analyst', 'Reviews access governance evidence by checking entitlement lists, certification progress, SoD exceptions, remediation records, and access review outcomes for audit and risk teams.'),
  ('RF-CS-005-01', 'Security GRC Analyst', 'Supports cyber governance, risk, and compliance by mapping controls, collecting audit evidence, tracking policy exceptions, updating risk records, and preparing review-ready compliance artifacts.'),
  ('RF-CS-005-02', 'Technology Risk / Controls Testing Analyst', 'Tests technology controls by checking control design evidence, operating effectiveness samples, risk disposition notes, remediation plans, and reviewer handoffs without issuing audit signoff independently.'),
  ('RF-CS-005-03', 'GRC Platform / Audit Evidence Analyst', 'Maintains GRC or IRM platform evidence by updating control records, audit requests, risk issue fields, owner responses, and evidence packages used for governance and compliance review.'),
  ('RF-CS-006-01', 'OT Security Engineer / Specialist', 'Supports OT security engineering by reviewing segmentation, industrial control constraints, maintenance windows, monitoring coverage, and security changes that may affect plant or operational environments.'),
  ('RF-CS-006-02', 'OT Security Monitoring / Asset Analyst', 'Monitors OT security and asset evidence by validating OT asset records, event context, plant-impact signals, escalation triggers, and engineering handoffs under strict operational authority limits.'),
  ('RF-CS-006-03', 'IT/OT Security Architect / Consultant', 'Designs or advises IT/OT security controls by aligning segmentation, remote access, monitoring, maintenance-window, and plant-safety requirements with cyber-risk controls and operational continuity needs.'),
  ('RF-CS-008-01', 'Penetration Tester / VAPT Engineer', 'Performs authorized penetration testing and VAPT evidence production by validating scope, testing approved targets, documenting findings, preserving proof, and handing remediation evidence to owners.'),
  ('RF-CS-008-02', 'Vulnerability Assessment / Vulnerability Management Analyst', 'Coordinates vulnerability assessment and lifecycle closure by validating findings, tracking remediation, confirming retest evidence, and separating true residual risk from duplicate or already-mitigated issues.'),
  ('RF-CS-008-03', 'Red Team / BAS Specialist', 'Reviews red-team or BAS scenarios by checking attack-simulation scope, control response evidence, scenario outcomes, detection gaps, and remediation follow-up without granting unapproved offensive authority.'),
  ('RF-CYB-APPSEC-004', 'Application and Cloud Security Engineering', 'Improves application and cloud security by reviewing design, code, dependencies, configurations, APIs, and deployment controls for exploitable weaknesses. This role family supports secure engineering practices, validates security findings, guides remediation, and provides evidence that security risks were addressed before or after release.'),
  ('RF-CYB-GRC-005', 'Security GRC Evidence Support', 'Supports governance, risk, and compliance work by collecting control evidence, tracking policy exceptions, preparing audit artifacts, and mapping security activity to frameworks or client requirements. This role family keeps security compliance traceable without overstating technical control ownership.'),
  ('RF-CYB-IAM-003', 'Identity and Access Security', 'Controls identity and access risks by supporting user lifecycle, access reviews, privileged access, authentication policies, and entitlement evidence. This role family validates access requests, detects inappropriate permissions, coordinates remediation, and maintains auditable records for identity governance and security compliance.'),
  ('RF-CYB-IR-006', 'Incident Response Coordination', 'Coordinates confirmed or suspected cybersecurity incidents across detection, containment, communication, recovery, evidence control, and post-incident review. This role family manages timelines, stakeholder updates, action tracking, escalation paths, and recovery proof while specialists handle deep forensic or containment tasks as required.'),
  ('RF-CYB-SOC-001', 'SOC and Security Monitoring', 'Monitors security alerts, suspicious activity, endpoint signals, network events, and SIEM queues to detect potential threats and service risks. This role family triages alerts, enriches events, separates false positives from incidents, escalates validated threats, and maintains evidence for security operations review.'),
  ('RF-CYB-VULN-002', 'Vulnerability Management', 'Identifies, prioritizes, tracks, and verifies remediation of vulnerabilities across applications, infrastructure, cloud assets, and endpoints. This role family reviews scan results, validates exploitability context, coordinates patch or mitigation actions, and maintains closure evidence for risk and audit reporting.'),
  ('RF-DAT-ANENG-004', 'Analytics Engineering', 'Prepares governed analytical data models that connect raw platform data with business-ready metrics and reusable semantic layers. This role family builds transformations, validates lineage, manages metric definitions, tests analytical models, and supports consistent self-service analytics across teams.'),
  ('RF-DAT-BA-005', 'Business Analytics and Decision Support', 'Uses business questions, operational data, and analytical methods to explain performance, diagnose problems, and support decisions. This role family frames analysis, tests assumptions, prepares insights, quantifies trade-offs, and communicates recommendations with evidence that stakeholders can act on.'),
  ('RF-DAT-BI-002', 'BI Reporting and Visualization', 'Turns business data into usable reports, dashboards, metrics, and visual explanations for decision-makers. This role family gathers reporting requirements, defines measures, builds visualizations, validates numbers, documents assumptions, and ensures stakeholders can interpret trends without data misuse.'),
  ('RF-DAT-DQ-003', 'Data Quality and Reliability', 'Protects trust in data by detecting completeness, accuracy, timeliness, consistency, duplication, and rule-conformance issues across datasets. This role family monitors quality checks, investigates anomalies, coordinates source corrections, documents defects, and provides evidence that data is reliable enough for downstream use.'),
  ('RF-DAT-ENG-001', 'Data Engineering', 'Builds and operates data pipelines, ingestion jobs, transformations, storage layers, and data movement patterns that supply reliable datasets to analytics and applications. This role family manages source connectivity, schema changes, orchestration, performance, and pipeline failure recovery with clear lineage evidence.'),
  ('RF-DCI-CAP-004', 'Capacity and Colocation Readiness Support', 'Supports capacity planning and colocation readiness by checking space, power, cooling, rack availability, cross-connect needs, customer requirements, and implementation dependencies. This role family prepares readiness evidence so sales, delivery, facility, and customer teams can commit to feasible deployments.'),
  ('RF-DCI-FAC-001', 'Data Centre Facility Operations', 'Maintains the physical facility conditions that keep data centre services running, including power, cooling, fire systems, space readiness, access procedures, and maintenance coordination. This role family monitors facility alarms, supports planned work, records incidents, and protects uptime through disciplined operational checks.'),
  ('RF-DCI-HW-002', 'Server and Rack Operations', 'Handles physical server, rack, cabling, hardware replacement, asset movement, and remote-hands activities inside data centre environments. This role family follows controlled procedures, updates asset evidence, coordinates with NOC or customer teams, and ensures hardware work does not create avoidable service risk.'),
  ('RF-DCI-NOC-003', 'Data Centre NOC Monitoring', 'Monitors data centre systems, infrastructure alerts, customer circuits, device status, environmental indicators, and incident queues from a centralized operations view. This role family triages alarms, confirms scope, escalates faults, tracks restoration, and records service-impact evidence for operational continuity.'),
  ('RF-DCI-SEC-005', 'Physical Security and Compliance Evidence Support', 'Supports physical security and compliance in data centre environments by controlling visitor records, access evidence, CCTV or guard-process records, audit artifacts, and policy exception tracking. This role family ensures facility access and compliance proof are complete, traceable, and ready for customer or regulatory review.'),
  ('RF-ERD-EMB-001', 'Embedded and Product Software Engineering', 'Develops software that runs inside devices, machines, instruments, vehicles, or connected products where hardware behaviour and software timing are tightly linked. This role family works on firmware, drivers, control logic, interfaces, diagnostics, and embedded feature updates while respecting reliability, safety, and product constraints.'),
  ('RF-ERD-PLM-002', 'Product Lifecycle Engineering', 'Supports engineering product lifecycle activities from design change to configuration, versioning, documentation, compliance evidence, and production handoff. This role family manages product records, engineering change requests, BOM alignment, lifecycle status, and coordination between design, manufacturing, quality, and support stakeholders.'),
  ('RF-ERD-QA-003', 'Engineering Verification and Validation', 'Verifies and validates engineered products or embedded systems against requirements, design intent, safety constraints, and performance expectations. This role family prepares test plans, executes bench or system tests, records evidence, tracks non-conformities, and supports engineering release decisions with traceable validation proof.'),
  ('RF-ERD-REL-004', 'Engineering Release and Configuration Support', 'Controls engineering release packages by checking version consistency, configuration records, drawing or software baselines, change approvals, and release documentation. This role family prevents uncontrolled product changes by maintaining traceable configuration evidence and coordinating handoff to manufacturing, service, or customer teams.'),
  ('RF-GAS-OPS', 'Gas Turbine / CCGT Operations and Maintenance', 'Handles gas turbine / CCGT operations, maintenance, commissioning support, and troubleshooting within gas-only scope.'),
  ('RF-HYDRO-LARGE-OPS', 'Large Hydro Station O&M', 'Handles large hydro station O&M across shift operations and civil, electrical, and mechanical maintenance.'),
  ('RF-IM-001', 'Manufacturing / Process Engineering', 'Junior manufacturing and process engineering roles support equipment industrialization by converting design, BOM and tooling inputs into process-route checks, inspection points and shopfloor-ready documentation under supervision.'),
  ('RF-IM-002', 'Auto Component Manufacturing Engineering', 'Junior auto component manufacturing roles support APQP, PPAP, control-plan checks, trial-run records and line-quality evidence for OEM component launch and production release activities.'),
  ('RF-IM-003', 'Electrical Equipment Manufacturing and Test Engineering', 'Junior electrical equipment manufacturing roles support transformer, motor, switchgear or panel build verification by checking BOM, drawings, rating details, wiring evidence and FAT/test records.'),
  ('RF-IM-004', 'Electronics Manufacturing and Test Engineering', 'Junior electronics manufacturing roles support PCB/EMS assembly by checking kitting, ESD records, AOI/test results, component traceability and rework routing evidence.'),
  ('RF-IM-005', 'Chemical Process / Plant Engineering', 'Junior chemical process roles support batch or continuous plant operations by checking COA, recipe readiness, DCS/PLC trends, shift logs, utility status and process deviation evidence.'),
  ('RF-IM-006', 'Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation', 'Junior pharma production and QA/QC roles support GMP execution by checking line clearance, BMR/BPR entries, cleanroom status, lab results, deviation notes and QA-ready handoff records.'),
  ('RF-IM-007A', 'Primary Metals / Steel Plant Operations Engineering', 'Junior primary metals roles support furnace, caster, rolling and maintenance operations by checking heat plans, melt chemistry, mill records, grade evidence and quality-hold documentation.'),
  ('RF-IM-007B', 'Foundry, Casting and Forging Engineering', 'Junior foundry and casting roles support melt, mould and pour control by checking pattern readiness, charge material, melt chemistry, pouring conditions and casting-lot records.'),
  ('RF-IM-007C', 'Fabricated Metal Products and Industrial Fabrication Engineering', 'Junior fabrication roles support cutting, fit-up, welding and QA handoff by checking drawings, material certificates, WPS/PQR references, travelers, weld maps and fit-up records.'),
  ('RF-IM-008', 'Cement / Mineral Plant Operations and E&I', 'Junior cement/mineral plant roles support kiln, mill, lab and instrumentation control by checking raw mix, setpoints, clinker/cement samples, grinding records, calibration and dispatch-quality evidence.'),
  ('RF-IM-009', 'Aerospace/Defence Manufacturing and NPI', 'Junior aerospace/defence manufacturing roles support NPI and configuration-controlled production by checking design data, supplier packages, tooling evidence, FAI records and documentation release packs.'),
  ('RF-ITS-APPDEV-001', 'Application Development and Modernization', 'Designs, builds, enhances, and modernizes client or enterprise applications across web, mobile, API, and legacy platforms. This role family converts business requirements into maintainable software, supports migration from older stacks, and ensures application changes are tested, documented, and ready for controlled release.'),
  ('RF-ITS-INTEG-002', 'Enterprise Integration and Implementation', 'Implements enterprise systems and connects applications through APIs, middleware, data flows, and configuration-led deployment activities. This role family coordinates solution setup, integration testing, environment readiness, cutover support, and client handoff evidence for business-critical implementations.'),
  ('RF-ITS-ITSM-004', 'Application Support and ITSM Operations', 'Keeps live applications stable by handling incidents, service requests, access issues, monitoring alerts, and operational handoffs through ITSM workflows. This role family performs first-level diagnosis, coordinates escalation, verifies recovery, and maintains service records for production applications.'),
  ('RF-ITS-QA-003', 'Client Application Quality Assurance', 'Validates client application behaviour against requirements, acceptance criteria, defect history, and release risks before delivery. This role family prepares test cases, executes functional and regression testing, documents defects, verifies fixes, and provides quality evidence for release decisions.'),
  ('RF-NUCLEAR-OPS-MAINT', 'Nuclear Operations and Maintenance Support', 'Handles supervised nuclear operations and maintenance support with strict non-regulatory authority boundaries.'),
  ('RF-SOLAR-UTILITY-OPS', 'Utility Solar Plant O&M and Performance', 'Handles utility-scale solar plant O&M, performance monitoring, SCADA/substation coordination, and site operations.'),
  ('RF-SWP-DEVOPS-005', 'Product DevOps and Release Operations', 'Runs the operational layer that packages, deploys, monitors, and stabilizes product releases across environments. This role family manages CI/CD readiness, deployment windows, rollback planning, environment configuration, release notes, and post-release verification for SaaS or software product platforms.'),
  ('RF-SWP-ENG-002', 'SaaS Product Engineering', 'Builds and improves cloud-based software products with attention to scalability, usability, security, maintainability, and release reliability. This role family develops product features, services, APIs, and interfaces while collaborating with product, QA, design, DevOps, and support teams across iterative release cycles.'),
  ('RF-SWP-PM-001', 'Software Product Management', 'Shapes software product direction by translating customer needs, market signals, usage data, and stakeholder priorities into roadmap, backlog, and release decisions. This role family defines product outcomes, clarifies requirements, manages trade-offs, and ensures engineering work connects to measurable customer and business value.'),
  ('RF-SWP-QA-003', 'Product Quality Engineering', 'Assures product quality across feature changes, regression scope, automation coverage, release readiness, and customer-impacting defect patterns. This role family designs product test strategy, validates workflows, automates repeat checks, confirms fixes, and supplies release-quality evidence to engineering and product teams.'),
  ('RF-SWP-SUPPORT-004', 'Product Support and Defect Triage', 'Handles product issues reported by customers, internal users, monitoring systems, and support channels by separating usage questions from defects and service-impacting failures. This role family reproduces issues, gathers logs, validates workarounds, routes defects to engineering, and confirms resolution with clear customer-facing evidence.'),
  ('RF-WIND-OPS', 'Wind Turbine O&M and Condition Monitoring', 'Handles onshore wind turbine O&M, turbine service, condition monitoring, and blade inspection/repair work.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-01-01', 'Critical Facility Engineer', 'Critical Facility Engineer is responsible for power, cooling, alarms and MOP execution for shared halls. Owns power, cooling, alarms and MOP execution for shared halls; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with MOP; alarm ticket; generator run log using DCIM; BMS; SCADA; CMMS. Support critical-facility monitoring, MOP/EOP/SOP evidence, maintenance coordination and incident escalation only; no electrical/mechanical sign-off, MOP approval or safety certification ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-01-02', 'Data Centre Operations Technician', 'Data Centre Operations Technician is responsible for rack-side inspection, rounds, equipment checks and escort support. Owns rack-side inspection, rounds, equipment checks and escort support; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with round sheet; access log; work-order closure using DCIM; access-control; ticketing. Support critical-facility monitoring, MOP/EOP/SOP evidence, maintenance coordination and incident escalation only; no electrical/mechanical sign-off, MOP approval or safety certification ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-01-03', 'Customer Operations Specialist', 'Customer Operations Specialist is responsible for remote-hands requests and customer work coordination. Owns remote-hands requests and customer work coordination; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with remote-hands ticket; cage photo evidence; closure note using customer portal; ticketing; access-control. Support access, ticket, remote-hands and interconnection coordination only; no unauthorized customer equipment, network change or security override.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-01-04', 'Interconnection Technician', 'Interconnection Technician is responsible for cross-connect patching, labeling and test evidence. Owns cross-connect patching, labeling and test evidence; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with cross-connect order; patch record; test result using cross-connect system; label printer; tester. Support access, ticket, remote-hands and interconnection coordination only; no unauthorized customer equipment, network change or security override.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-02-01', 'Data Center Engineering Operations Engineer', 'Data Center Engineering Operations Engineer is responsible for critical infrastructure operation and incident response. Owns critical infrastructure operation and incident response; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with incident bridge notes; change record; energy trend using DCIM; CMMS; BMS; ITSM. Support critical-facility monitoring, MOP/EOP/SOP evidence, maintenance coordination and incident escalation only; no electrical/mechanical sign-off, MOP approval or safety certification ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-02-02', 'Hardware Operations Technician', 'Hardware Operations Technician is responsible for server rack installation, cable checks and asset handover. Owns server rack installation, cable checks and asset handover; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with rack acceptance note; asset tag; port map using asset CMDB; deployment tool; ticketing. Support critical-facility monitoring, MOP/EOP/SOP evidence, maintenance coordination and incident escalation only; no electrical/mechanical sign-off, MOP approval or safety certification ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-02-03', 'Commissioning Manager', 'Commissioning Manager is responsible for testing, punch-list and system launch readiness. Owns testing, punch-list and system launch readiness; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with commissioning checklist; test script; punch-list using commissioning tracker; document control. Support critical-facility monitoring, MOP/EOP/SOP evidence, maintenance coordination and incident escalation only; no electrical/mechanical sign-off, MOP approval or safety certification ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-02-04', 'Electrical or Mechanical Engineer', 'Electrical or Mechanical Engineer is responsible for power distribution, cooling system checks and quality evidence. Owns power distribution, cooling system checks and quality evidence; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with single-line check; cooling trend; maintenance report using BMS; SCADA; CMMS. Support critical-facility monitoring, MOP/EOP/SOP evidence, maintenance coordination and incident escalation only; no electrical/mechanical sign-off, MOP approval or safety certification ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-03-01', 'Data Centre Operations Engineer', 'Data Centre Operations Engineer is responsible for server asset control, access records and facility coordination. Owns server asset control, access records and facility coordination; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with asset register; access approval; incident ticket using CMDB; access-control; ITSM. Support ITSM, backup, access, monitoring and escalation workflows only; no cyber incident command, cloud architecture ownership or root-access assumption unless evidenced.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-03-02', 'NOC Analyst', 'NOC Analyst is responsible for monitoring alerts, escalation and communication bridges. Owns monitoring alerts, escalation and communication bridges; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with alert triage note; escalation log; SLA update using monitoring console; ITSM; chat bridge. Support ITSM, backup, access, monitoring and escalation workflows only; no cyber incident command, cloud architecture ownership or root-access assumption unless evidenced.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-03-03', 'Systems Administrator', 'Systems Administrator is responsible for backup, patch and recovery support for hosted systems. Owns backup, patch and recovery support for hosted systems; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with backup report; change ticket; recovery test note using backup platform; server console; ITSM. Support ITSM, backup, access, monitoring and escalation workflows only; no cyber incident command, cloud architecture ownership or root-access assumption unless evidenced.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-03-04', 'Facilities Support Engineer', 'Facilities Support Engineer is responsible for UPS, cooling and environmental checks for private rooms. Owns UPS, cooling and environmental checks for private rooms; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with UPS log; temperature reading; maintenance ticket using BMS-lite; meter log; CMMS. Support ITSM, backup, access, monitoring and escalation workflows only; no cyber incident command, cloud architecture ownership or root-access assumption unless evidenced.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-04-01', 'Remote Operations Analyst', 'Remote Operations Analyst is responsible for edge-node alarms, utilization trend and field dispatch. Owns edge-node alarms, utilization trend and field dispatch; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with remote alarm ticket; capacity watch note; escalation log using remote monitoring; ticketing; NMS. Benchmark/global-standards module reference only; no India-current standalone pathway claim without stronger India role evidence.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-04-02', 'Edge Site Technician', 'Edge Site Technician is responsible for modular enclosure access, inspection and vendor repair. Owns modular enclosure access, inspection and vendor repair; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with site access log; inspection checklist; warranty note using field-service app; EMS/BMS-lite. Benchmark/global-standards module reference only; no India-current standalone pathway claim without stronger India role evidence.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-04-03', 'Field Service Engineer', 'Field Service Engineer is responsible for power/cooling module replacement and site restoration evidence. Owns power/cooling module replacement and site restoration evidence; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with repair report; component swap note; closure photo using field-service app; test meter; ticketing. Benchmark/global-standards role reference only; no India-current standalone pathway claim without stronger India role evidence.'),
  ('ROLE-DC-04-04', 'Network Support Engineer', 'Network Support Engineer is responsible for latency evidence, port checks and network escalation support. Owns latency evidence, port checks and network escalation support; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with latency record; port test; capacity note using NMS; packet tester; ticketing. Benchmark/global-standards role reference only; no India-current standalone pathway claim without stronger India role evidence.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-001', 'Upstream geoscience / petroleum engineering', 'Covers subsurface evaluation and reservoir-development support for oil and gas assets, including seismic interpretation, formation understanding, well-data review, reserve or production potential assessment, and field-development evidence. The role family connects geological, geophysical, reservoir, and production data so exploration and development decisions are technically grounded.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-002A', 'Operator-side drilling / well operations', 'Manages operator-side drilling and well-execution activity from planning handoff through rig operations, well control readiness, daily drilling performance, contractor coordination, and well-integrity evidence. The role family keeps drilling work aligned with safety, cost, schedule, regulatory, and reservoir objectives while controlling operational risk at the wellsite and office-support level.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-002B', 'Oilfield services / third-party well services', 'Delivers specialist third-party well services such as cementing, logging, directional drilling, stimulation, testing, completion support, wireline, coiled tubing, or production enhancement. The role family works at the interface of service equipment, field crews, operator programs, job-design instructions, safety controls, data capture, and post-job evidence required to prove service quality.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-003', 'Refinery process and production operations', 'Runs and monitors refinery process units that convert crude oil and intermediate streams into fuels and other refined products. The role family covers unit start-up support, process parameter monitoring, shift operations, production targets, quality checks, energy efficiency signals, abnormal condition response, and coordination with maintenance, laboratory, safety, and planning teams.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-004A', 'Gas Transmission / LNG Terminal Operations', 'Operates gas transmission and LNG terminal systems that receive, store, regasify, compress, meter, and move natural gas safely across high-pressure networks. The role family manages terminal readiness, gas quality, custody-transfer records, pipeline pressure conditions, equipment status, dispatch coordination, emergency response, and customer or grid supply continuity.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-004B', 'CGD / CNG / PNG Network Operations', 'Supports city gas distribution operations across CNG stations, PNG networks, metering points, pressure regulating stations, customer connections, and emergency-response workflows. The role family ensures safe and reliable gas delivery to residential, commercial, industrial, and mobility users through network monitoring, field coordination, leak or pressure issue response, and service-restoration evidence.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-005', 'Pipeline / terminal / storage integrity operations', 'Maintains the integrity and reliability of pipelines, terminals, tanks, loading systems, and storage assets used for crude, gas, refined products, or petrochemical movement. The role family covers inspection evidence, corrosion or leak-risk monitoring, pigging or testing coordination, tank and terminal checks, permit-controlled work, and escalation of asset-integrity threats before they become safety or supply incidents.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-006', 'LPG bottling and distribution operations', 'Coordinates LPG bottling, cylinder handling, bulk receipt, filling-line operations, quality and safety checks, dispatch planning, distributor supply, and stock reconciliation. The role family protects safe cylinder movement and reliable market supply by managing plant operations, transport handoffs, equipment readiness, statutory checks, and exception closure for bottling and distribution workflows.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-007', 'Petrochemical / polymer process operations', 'Runs and controls petrochemical and polymer production processes that convert hydrocarbon feedstocks into chemicals, polymers, intermediates, or specialty materials. The role family monitors reactors, process conditions, feedstock quality, product specifications, catalyst or additive usage, utilities, safety interlocks, and production evidence needed for stable output and quality compliance.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-008A', 'Retail Outlet / Dealer Operations', 'Manages fuel retail outlet and dealer operations, including sales readiness, stock and dispensing checks, forecourt safety, customer service, dealer compliance, payment or reconciliation controls, and brand-standard execution. The role family connects depot supply, outlet operations, customer experience, and audit evidence so retail fuel delivery remains safe, compliant, and commercially reliable.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-008B', 'Aviation / Marine / Institutional Fuel Operations', 'Supports specialized fuel supply to aviation, marine, defence, industrial, fleet, and institutional customers where product quality, custody transfer, scheduling, and safety controls are critical. The role family manages fuel receipt, storage, filtration or testing evidence, loading or bunkering coordination, documentation, customer handoff, and incident-free service continuity for high-accountability fuel operations.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-008C', 'Lubricants Sales / Technical Support', 'Combines lubricant product knowledge, customer application understanding, field troubleshooting, and sales support for automotive, industrial, marine, and specialty lubricant users. The role family supports product selection, trial monitoring, equipment-condition feedback, dealer or distributor enablement, complaint handling, and value-based customer guidance using technical and commercial evidence.'),
  ('ROLE-SIGNAL-009', 'EPC project engineering and construction', 'Plans, engineers, constructs, and commissions oil, gas, pipeline, refinery, petrochemical, terminal, or energy infrastructure projects through EPC delivery. The role family coordinates engineering drawings, procurement status, construction sequencing, contractor execution, quality inspection, safety compliance, punch-list closure, and handover documentation so assets are built to specification and ready for operation.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB001-DES', 'Leather Recipe, Shade, Finish, and Sample Development', 'Recipe control, shade matching, finish sample preparation, buyer correction closure. Work objects: buyer shade cards, recipe sheets, finish trials, leather samples, approval comments. Evidence outputs: shade card, recipe sheet, finish trial sheet, buyer approval comment log.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB001-MERCH', 'Finished Leather Buyer / Export Coordination', 'Buyer communication, sample approval tracking, controlled export documentation support. Work objects: buyer sample comments, finished leather order files, traceability packs, export handoff records. Evidence outputs: buyer sample comment tracker, order file, export documentation handoff.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB001-PROD', 'Tannery Batch Processing and Finishing Line Control', 'Batch processing, drum control, finishing line execution, lot movement control. Work objects: wet-blue/crust lots, drum logs, chemical batches, finishing line records, lot cards. Evidence outputs: drum processing log, lot card, finishing line record, chemical batch record.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB001-QA', 'Leather Lab, Traceability, ETP, and Compliance QA', 'Lab testing, shade/thickness checks, traceability record control, etp and mrsl evidence support. Work objects: leather test reports, traceability packs, ETP logs, restricted substance evidence. Evidence outputs: leather test report, traceability file, ETP log, restricted substance evidence file.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB002-DES', 'Footwear Last, Pattern, CAD, Upper, Outsole, and Sample Development', 'Last/pattern development, sample correction, upper/outsole specification, buyer sample closure. Work objects: last specifications, CAD patterns, upper materials, outsole samples, size grading sheets. Evidence outputs: last specification, CAD pattern, size grading sheet, buyer sample comment tracker.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB002-MERCH', 'Footwear Merchandising, Buyer Coordination, Costing, and Shipment Handoff', 'Buyer communication, order file control, vendor follow-up, costing and export handoff. Work objects: order trackers, BOM costing sheets, buyer approvals, dispatch packs, shipment documentation. Evidence outputs: order tracker, BOM costing sheet, dispatch pack, buyer approval mail.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB002-PROD', 'Cutting, Stitching, Lasting, Sole Bonding, Finishing, and Packing Supervision', 'Line loading, cutting/stitching/lasting control, sole bonding, finishing and packing follow-up. Work objects: cutting issue slips, upper stitching plans, lasting checklists, sole bonding logs, WIP trackers. Evidence outputs: cutting issue slip, stitching line plan, lasting checklist, sole bonding log, WIP tracker.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB002-QA', 'Footwear AQL, BIS/QCO, Fit, Bond, and Buyer Inspection QA', 'Inspection planning, bond/fit check coordination, bis/qco checklist support, shipment readiness review. Work objects: AQL sheets, BIS/QCO checklists, bond tests, fit checks, defect logs, shipment readiness files. Evidence outputs: AQL sheet, BIS/QCO checklist, bond test, defect log, shipment readiness checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB003-DES', 'Polymeric Footwear Material, Mould, Outsole, and Sample Development', 'Material specification, mould sample development, outsole sample correction. Work objects: EVA/PU/PVC/rubber specs, mould designs, outsole samples, size/spec sheets. Evidence outputs: material specification sheet, mould design note, outsole sample tracker.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB003-MERCH', 'Polymeric Footwear Buyer / Supplier Coordination', 'Buyer/supplier communication, dispatch coordination, controlled order follow-up. Work objects: buyer requirement notes, supplier trackers, dispatch handoff files. Evidence outputs: supplier tracker, dispatch checklist, buyer approval mail.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB003-PROD', 'Material Mixing, Moulding, Curing, Injection/Compression, and Line Control', 'Mixing, moulding, curing, injection/compression line control, dispatch readiness. Work objects: material mixing sheets, mould setup cards, curing records, injection/compression cycle logs. Evidence outputs: material mixing sheet, mould setup card, curing record, cycle log.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB003-QA', 'Polymeric Footwear QCO, Outsole Testing, Visual Defect, and Dispatch QA', 'Qco checklist support, outsole testing, visual defect review, dispatch inspection. Work objects: BIS/QCO checklists, outsole inspection records, curing defect records, dispatch checklists. Evidence outputs: BIS/QCO checklist, outsole inspection record, curing defect record, dispatch checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB004-DES', 'Bag, Wallet, Belt, Pattern, Hardware, Trim, and Sample Development', 'Pattern and sample development, hardware/trim selection, buyer sample correction. Work objects: pattern panels, trim BOMs, lining specs, hardware specs, buyer sample comments. Evidence outputs: pattern panel sheet, trim BOM, lining spec, hardware spec, buyer comment tracker.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB004-MERCH', 'Leather Goods Merchandising, Buyer Comments, Costing, and Export Handoff', 'Buyer communication, costing support, order file control, export handoff. Work objects: order trackers, BOM costing sheets, buyer comments, export packing handoffs. Evidence outputs: order tracker, BOM costing sheet, buyer comment tracker, export packing handoff.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB004-PROD', 'Cutting, Skiving, Stitching, Edge Painting, Hardware Fitment, and Assembly Supervision', 'Cutting, skiving, stitching, edge finish, hardware fitment and assembly control. Work objects: cutting panel issues, skiving instructions, stitching records, edge paint inspections, hardware fitment checklists. Evidence outputs: cutting panel issue, skiving instruction, stitching record, edge paint inspection, hardware fitment checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB004-QA', 'Leather Goods AQL, Stitch, Finish, Hardware, and Packaging QA', 'Aql inspection, stitch/finish/hardware checks, packing and buyer release support. Work objects: AQL sheets, edge finish records, stitch inspections, hardware placement checks, packing files. Evidence outputs: AQL sheet, edge finish record, stitch inspection, hardware placement check, packing checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB005-DES', 'Leather Garment/Glove Pattern, Fit Sample, and Panel Development', 'Pattern development, panel matching, fit sample correction, buyer comment closure. Work objects: pattern sheets, panel matching records, fit sample comments, size/measurement specs. Evidence outputs: pattern sheet, panel matching record, fit sample comment tracker, measurement spec.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB005-MERCH', 'Leather Garment/Glove Merchandising, Buyer Fit Comments, and Export Coordination', 'Buyer communication, fit comment closure, order file control, export coordination. Work objects: buyer fit comments, order trackers, sample approvals, export handoff files. Evidence outputs: buyer fit comment tracker, order tracker, sample approval mail, export packing handoff.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB005-PROD', 'Cutting, Sewing, Lining, Measurement, and Packing Supervision', 'Cutting, sewing, lining attachment, measurement follow-up, packing control. Work objects: cutting markers, sewing line records, lining checks, measurement sheets, packing files. Evidence outputs: cutting marker, sewing line record, lining attachment check, measurement sheet.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB005-QA', 'Garment/Glove Measurement, Fit, Stitch, AQL, and Buyer Release QA', 'Measurement inspection, fit/stitch/aql checks, buyer release support. Work objects: measurement inspection sheets, AQL sheets, fit correction trackers, defect logs, export packing files. Evidence outputs: measurement inspection sheet, AQL sheet, fit correction tracker, defect log, export packing checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB006-DES', 'Saddlery/Harness Strap, Pattern, Hardware, and Sample Preparation', 'Strap pattern preparation, hardware sample coordination, controlled buyer correction. Work objects: strap templates, buckle/rivet specs, harness samples, buyer quality notes. Evidence outputs: strap cutting template, buckle/rivet specification, harness sample, buyer quality note.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB006-MERCH', 'Controlled Saddlery/Harness Buyer and Export Coordination', 'Controlled buyer/export documentation support, order follow-up, packing handoff. Work objects: buyer documentation files, quality handoff notes, export packing checklists. Evidence outputs: buyer documentation file, quality handoff note, export packing checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB006-PROD', 'Heavy-Leather Cutting, Strap Preparation, Stitching, Riveting, and Assembly', 'Heavy-leather cutting, strap preparation, stitching, riveting, buckle setting, assembly control. Work objects: heavy-leather cutting sheets, strap preparation records, rivet setting checklists, assembly logs. Evidence outputs: heavy-leather cutting sheet, strap preparation record, rivet setting checklist, assembly log.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB006-QA', 'Stitch Strength, Hardware Safety, Pull Test, and Buyer Quality Inspection', 'Stitch strength inspection, hardware safety checks, pull test evidence, export quality release support. Work objects: stitch strength inspections, hardware safety checklists, pull test reports, export packing files. Evidence outputs: stitch strength inspection, hardware safety checklist, pull test report, export packing checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB007-DES', 'Upper, Component BOM, Insole/Outsole, and Supplier Sample Development', 'Upper/component sample development, supplier specification control, buyer component correction. Work objects: component BOMs, upper patterns, supplier specs, bonding samples, buyer component comments. Evidence outputs: component BOM, upper pattern, supplier spec, bonding sample, buyer component comment.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB007-MERCH', 'Footwear Component Buyer, Supplier, and Dispatch Coordination', 'Buyer/supplier coordination, component dispatch follow-up, buyer handoff documentation. Work objects: buyer handoff records, supplier trackers, dispatch checklists, approval mails. Evidence outputs: buyer component handoff record, supplier tracker, dispatch checklist, approval mail.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB007-PROD', 'Upper Cutting, Skiving, Stitching, Component Preparation, and Dispatch Control', 'Upper cutting, skiving, stitching, component preparation, dispatch control. Work objects: upper cutting issue slips, skiving records, upper stitching plans, component batch cards. Evidence outputs: upper cutting issue slip, skiving record, upper stitching line plan, component batch card.'),
  ('ROLE-SUB007-QA', 'Component Supplier Quality, Bonding, Dispatch Inspection, and Buyer Handoff QA', 'Supplier quality checks, bonding validation, component inspection, buyer handoff qa. Work objects: supplier quality checks, bonding tests, component inspections, dispatch checklists. Evidence outputs: supplier quality check, bonding test record, component inspection sheet, dispatch checklist.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-01-01', 'Warehouse Operations Manager', 'Warehouse Operations Manager is responsible for dock flow, GRN, put-away and dispatch readiness. Owns dock flow, GRN, put-away and dispatch readiness; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with GRN pack; productivity dashboard; safety walk record using WMS; ERP; barcode scanner. Support warehouse execution, dock/WMS/inventory/dispatch evidence and escalation only; no final inventory adjustment, audit sign-off or statutory responsibility.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-01-02', 'Inventory Control Executive', 'Inventory Control Executive is responsible for cycle counts, bin adjustments and client stock variance. Owns cycle counts, bin adjustments and client stock variance; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with cycle-count report; adjustment note; stock ledger using WMS; handheld scanner; client portal. Support warehouse execution, dock/WMS/inventory/dispatch evidence and escalation only; no final inventory adjustment, audit sign-off or statutory responsibility.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-01-03', 'Inbound and Outbound Supervisor', 'Inbound and Outbound Supervisor is responsible for shift-level receiving, picking, packing and dispatch closure. Owns shift-level receiving, picking, packing and dispatch closure; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with dock plan; pick list; dispatch manifest using WMS; dock scheduler; transport portal. Support warehouse execution, dock/WMS/inventory/dispatch evidence and escalation only; no final inventory adjustment, audit sign-off or statutory responsibility.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-01-04', 'WMS Process Analyst', 'WMS Process Analyst is responsible for master data, scan compliance, exception queues and SLA reports. Owns master data, scan compliance, exception queues and SLA reports; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with exception report; SLA dashboard; root cause note using WMS; BI dashboard; spreadsheet. Support WMS evidence, exception queues, scan compliance and reporting only; no WMS product ownership, ERP configuration authority or system architecture ownership.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-02-01', 'Fulfilment Operations Manager', 'Fulfilment Operations Manager is responsible for station productivity, order cut-off and safety execution. Owns station productivity, order cut-off and safety execution; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with shift plan; station board; productivity variance note using fulfilment execution system; labor scheduler. Support warehouse execution, dock/WMS/inventory/dispatch evidence and escalation only; no final inventory adjustment, audit sign-off or statutory responsibility.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-02-02', 'Process Assistant', 'Process Assistant is responsible for stow, pick, pack or sort process adherence on assigned line. Owns stow, pick, pack or sort process adherence on assigned line; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with process audit; station roster; defect log using handheld scanner; station console. Support warehouse execution, dock/WMS/inventory/dispatch evidence and escalation only; no final inventory adjustment, audit sign-off or statutory responsibility.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-02-03', 'Sortation Supervisor', 'Sortation Supervisor is responsible for parcel bagging, route staging and carrier handoff. Owns parcel bagging, route staging and carrier handoff; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with route manifest; bag close record; missed-cutoff note using sortation console; carrier portal. Support warehouse execution, dock/WMS/inventory/dispatch evidence and escalation only; no final inventory adjustment, audit sign-off or statutory responsibility.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-02-04', 'Returns Quality Lead', 'Returns Quality Lead is responsible for return inspection, disposition and restock evidence. Owns return inspection, disposition and restock evidence; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with QC disposition; restock ticket; damage evidence using returns module; image capture; WMS. Support returns quality triage and disposition evidence only; no final QA release or product disposition authority unless explicitly evidenced.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-03-01', 'Cold Chain Operations Manager', 'Cold Chain Operations Manager is responsible for cold-room storage plan, FEFO flow and reefer dispatch. Owns cold-room storage plan, FEFO flow and reefer dispatch; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with temperature dashboard; FEFO pick plan; dispatch log using WMS; cold-room BMS; data logger. Support cold-room/reefer execution, temperature logs, FEFO and excursion escalation only; no GDP certification, QA release or quality-head authority.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-03-02', 'Temperature Compliance Executive', 'Temperature Compliance Executive is responsible for temperature excursion review and evidence pack preparation. Owns temperature excursion review and evidence pack preparation; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with excursion report; deviation note; logger download using IoT logger platform; QA documentation system. Support cold-room/reefer execution, temperature logs, FEFO and excursion escalation only; no GDP certification, QA release or quality-head authority.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-03-03', 'QA Release Coordinator', 'QA Release Coordinator is responsible for quality hold/release coordination for temperature-sensitive stock. Owns quality hold/release coordination for temperature-sensitive stock; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with QA release note; hold log; batch trace using QMS; WMS; batch tracker. Support cold-room/reefer execution, temperature logs, FEFO and excursion escalation only; no GDP certification, QA release or quality-head authority.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-03-04', 'Reefer Dispatch Planner', 'Reefer Dispatch Planner is responsible for vehicle pre-cool, route assignment and temperature handoff. Owns vehicle pre-cool, route assignment and temperature handoff; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with pre-cool record; route docket; seal log using TMS; reefer telematics; WMS. Support cold-room/reefer execution, temperature logs, FEFO and excursion escalation only; no GDP certification, QA release or quality-head authority.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-04-01', 'Godown Manager', 'Godown Manager is responsible for receipt, stacking, preservation and issue of commodity lots. Owns receipt, stacking, preservation and issue of commodity lots; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with lot stack card; stock register; receipt note using stock register; weighbridge system. Support commodity storage documentation, stock register, fumigation/inspection coordination and warehouse receipt evidence only; no statutory issuer, regulator, licensed surveyor or final grading authority.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-04-02', 'Commodity Quality Surveyor', 'Commodity Quality Surveyor is responsible for moisture, infestation and sample evidence for stored lots. Owns moisture, infestation and sample evidence for stored lots; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with moisture sheet; inspection note; sample tag using moisture meter; inspection app. Support returns quality triage and disposition evidence only; no final QA release or product disposition authority unless explicitly evidenced.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-04-03', 'Warehouse Receipt Executive', 'Warehouse Receipt Executive is responsible for receipt evidence and pledge documentation support. Owns receipt evidence and pledge documentation support; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with warehouse receipt; pledge pack; audit trail using receipt platform; document repository. Support commodity storage documentation, stock register, fumigation/inspection coordination and warehouse receipt evidence only; no statutory issuer, regulator, licensed surveyor or final grading authority.'),
  ('ROLE-WH-04-04', 'Fumigation and Stock Audit Coordinator', 'Fumigation and Stock Audit Coordinator is responsible for pest-control schedule, fumigation evidence and stock verification. Owns pest-control schedule, fumigation evidence and stock verification; escalates boundary issues; maintains source-backed artifacts. The role works with fumigation log; stock audit sheet; exception memo using pest-control log; spreadsheet. Support commodity storage documentation, stock register, fumigation/inspection coordination and warehouse receipt evidence only; no statutory issuer, regulator, licensed surveyor or final grading authority.'),
