  ('TEL-RF-001', 'Mobile Access Field and RAN Operations', 'Manages the field-facing operation of mobile access and radio access network sites, including cell-site checks, RF equipment readiness, alarm response, basic fault isolation, and restoration coordination with NOC, field, and vendor teams. The role family keeps mobile coverage and access quality stable at the site and cluster level.'),
  ('TEL-RF-002', 'Mobile Core and Network Assurance', 'Monitors and assures the mobile core network that enables voice, data, messaging, roaming, subscriber sessions, and service continuity. The role family works with alarms, KPIs, incident queues, change windows, and root-cause evidence to restore or protect customer-impacting network services.'),
  ('TEL-RF-003', 'FTTH/Fiber Access Deployment', 'Plans, coordinates, and validates last-mile fiber rollout from distribution points to customer or building termination points. The role family covers route readiness, splicing and termination evidence, ONT installation support, test-result validation, and blocker escalation before service handover.'),
  ('TEL-RF-004', 'FWA/Home Connectivity Enablement', 'Enables fixed wireless access and home broadband connectivity through customer-premise device setup, signal-position checks, activation support, and first-level troubleshooting. The role family connects technical network conditions with practical home installation decisions and customer guidance.'),
  ('TEL-RF-005', 'Tower Site and Passive Infrastructure Operations', 'Oversees passive telecom site infrastructure such as towers, shelters, power systems, batteries, DG sets, cooling, grounding, access security, and site maintenance readiness. The role family ensures network equipment has safe, powered, compliant, and physically reliable operating conditions.'),
  ('TEL-RF-006', 'RoW and Infrastructure Permissions', 'Coordinates right-of-way, permissions, local authority documentation, landlord or society approvals, and infrastructure clearance needed for telecom rollout or maintenance. The role family reduces deployment delays by aligning field plans with legal, civic, safety, and stakeholder approval requirements.'),
  ('TEL-RF-007', 'IP Network Operations', 'Operates and assures IP network layers that carry enterprise, broadband, mobile, and backbone traffic across routers, switches, firewalls, and routing domains. The role family handles monitoring, ticket triage, configuration checks, capacity signals, route incidents, and controlled escalation.'),
  ('TEL-RF-008', 'ISP Subscriber Internet Assurance Operations', 'Assures internet service quality for ISP subscribers by handling connectivity complaints, session issues, speed or latency symptoms, CPE status, access-node indicators, and service restoration workflows. The role family links customer symptoms to network evidence and supportable corrective actions.'),
  ('TEL-RF-009', 'Enterprise Managed WAN and SD-WAN Delivery', 'Delivers and supports managed WAN and SD-WAN services for business customers across branches, cloud access, underlay links, policies, devices, and service assurance commitments. The role family coordinates implementation evidence, configuration readiness, partner handoffs, and post-deployment service stability.'),
  ('TEL-RF-010', 'Enterprise Connectivity Service Delivery', 'Manages the delivery of enterprise connectivity products such as leased lines, internet links, MPLS, DIA, point-to-point circuits, and access provisioning. The role family coordinates order validation, feasibility, last-mile readiness, installation milestones, acceptance testing, and customer handover.'),
  ('TEL-RF-011', 'Optical Transport and Backhaul Operations', 'Operates optical transport and backhaul networks that move high-capacity traffic between sites, aggregation layers, data centers, and core nodes. The role family monitors fiber spans, DWDM or transport equipment, protection paths, alarms, capacity utilization, and service-impact restoration actions.'),
  ('TEL-RF-012', 'NLD/ILD Capacity and Interconnect Operations', 'Manages national long-distance, international long-distance, capacity, interconnect, and carrier-facing network operations. The role family tracks cross-network capacity, partner handoffs, routing or interconnect status, planned changes, utilization signals, and service continuity across operator boundaries.'),
  ('TEL-RF-013', 'Satellite Authorization and Frequency Coordination', 'Handles authorization, licensing support, spectrum or frequency coordination, regulatory documentation, and technical clearance for satellite communication services. The role family ensures satellite links and services operate within approved frequency, interference, and compliance boundaries.'),
  ('TEL-RF-014', 'VSAT and Satellite Managed Service Operations', 'Deploys and assures VSAT and satellite-managed connectivity for remote sites, enterprise locations, maritime, government, or backup communication use cases. The role family covers terminal setup, link checks, hub coordination, signal quality, incident response, SLA tracking, and customer service continuity.'),
  ('TEL-RF-015', 'PM-WANI PDO Coordination and Public Wi-Fi Operations', 'Coordinates public Wi-Fi operations under the PM-WANI ecosystem, including PDO onboarding, hotspot readiness, authentication flow support, usage monitoring, and issue escalation. The role family supports accessible public internet delivery while maintaining operational records and service reliability.'),
  ('TEL-RF-016', 'Radio Network Planning and Trunked Radio Operations', 'Plans, configures, and assures radio networks, including coverage design, channel planning, trunked radio systems, site parameters, interference checks, and operational support for mission or enterprise communication users. The role family balances spectrum efficiency, coverage reliability, and user-group service needs.'),
  ('TEL-RF-017', 'Cable Landing Station and Subsea Network Operations', 'Operates cable landing stations and subsea network interfaces that connect international submarine cable systems to terrestrial telecom networks. The role family manages landing-station equipment, power and facility readiness, protection paths, partner coordination, capacity handoff, and incident response.'),
  ('TEL-RF-018', 'Broadband Access Service Assurance Operations', 'Assures broadband access services across access networks, customer connectivity layers, CPE indicators, access-node health, complaint patterns, and restoration workflows. The role family focuses on maintaining reliable home or small-business broadband experience through evidence-led troubleshooting and service-quality checks.'),
  ('TLS-RF-001', 'Road Freight Dispatch & Transport Operations', 'Plan freight vehicle placement, coordinate route execution, track POD closure and resolve freight dispatch exceptions'),
  ('TLS-RF-002', 'Freight Fleet Compliance & Utilization', 'Maintain vehicle documentation, monitor utilization, maintenance and freight operating cost'),
  ('TLS-RF-003', 'Rail/Inland Terminal Operations', 'Coordinate rake/container loading, unloading, terminal turnaround, safety checks and container inventory handoff'),
  ('TLS-RF-004', 'Bulk Rail Dispatch & Commodity Logistics', 'Plan daily bulk dispatch, align wagon availability, loading safety and ERP dispatch records'),
  ('TLS-RF-005', 'Port Terminal Yard & Vessel/Cargo Operations', 'Coordinate yard equipment placement, loading/discharge, vessel/cargo movement and productivity reporting'),
  ('TLS-RF-006', 'CFS/ICD Gate & Documentation Control', 'Monitor in/out container movement, generate out-pass/RFID and prepare reports for customs/bond/shipping-line stakeholders'),
  ('TLS-RF-007', 'Coastal/Ocean Freight Operations', 'Book cargo space, track coastal/ocean shipment milestones, prepare documentation and coordinate port handoff'),
  ('TLS-RF-008', 'Inland Waterway Freight Coordination', 'Coordinate waterway/barge service planning, cargo readiness and multimodal handoff for inland routes'),
  ('TLS-RF-009', 'Air Freight Import/Export Operations', 'Execute air import/export shipments, coordinate airlines/agents/customers, manage carting/customs handoff and milestone tracking'),
  ('TLS-RF-010', 'Airport Cargo Terminal & Ground-Handling Interface', 'Coordinate cargo-terminal operations, ramp/load-control interfaces and safe aircraft/cargo turnaround handoffs'),
  ('TLS-RF-011', 'Ambient Warehouse & Inventory Operations', 'Coordinate receiving, putaway, inventory adjustments, dock activity and dispatch readiness'),
  ('TLS-RF-012', '3PL Fulfilment & Customer Operations', 'Coordinate pick/pack/dispatch services, customer SLA reporting and value-added service handoffs'),
  ('TLS-RF-013', 'CEP Hub, Sortation & Linehaul Operations', 'Coordinate parcel sortation, hub dispatch, linehaul handoff and exception control'),
  ('TLS-RF-014', 'Last-Mile Delivery & Returns Control', 'Coordinate final-mile delivery execution, courier partners, failed delivery resolution, POD and returns handoff'),
  ('TLS-RF-015', 'Food/Dairy/Frozen Cold Chain Operations', 'Maintain cold-room/reefer handling, monitor temperature logs, respond to excursions and preserve product integrity'),
  ('TLS-RF-016', 'Pharma/Biological Cold-Chain GDP Support', 'Support storage/distribution/transportation documentation, deviation reporting and vehicle/equipment control for pharma/biological cold chain'),
  ('TLS-RF-017', '4PL Control Tower & Lead Logistics Operations', 'Monitor shipment milestones, coordinate vendors, escalate exceptions and report customer service/performance status'),
  ('TLS-RF-018', 'Supply Chain Orchestration Analytics Support', 'Analyze vendor/carrier service, cost and exception patterns to support logistics network optimization')
